τριετῆ here = τριετηρικόν .
Trieterica (Ovid Remedia Amoris R. A. 593 ,
of Ovid's Metamorphoses M. VI .587 ;
of Vergil's Aeneid Verg. Aen. IV .302 ;
repetita triennia of Ovid's Metamorphoses Ov. M. IX .641 ;
τριετηρίς Eur. Bacch. 133;
Diod. III .65 , etc.) is what we should call a biennial festival, recurring in alternate years,
παρ’ ἔτος (Paus. VI .26.2 ,
VIII .23.1 , X .4.3 ).
Hence Statius' Achilleid Stat. A. I .595
Alternam renovare piae trieterida matres Consuerant.

